    "reasoning": "The tournament has 32 players, and in each round, the remaining players are paired uniformly at random. The probability that two specific players (Ava and Tiffany) meet at some point is computed by summing the probabilities they meet in each round. This sum equals 1/16, so the reduced fraction has denominator b = 16.\n\nWith b = 16, the inequality becomes: c - 0.1 < x^p * (1 - (1 + x)^{10}) / (1 + (1 + x)^{10}) < c + 0.1 for all x with 0 < x < 10^{-100}. For very small x, expand (1 + x)^{10} as 1 + 10x + ... . The expression approximates x^p * (-5x) = -5x^{p+1}. For this to be nearly constant (within 0.1 of an integer c) over the interval, the exponent of x must be zero, so p + 1 = 0, giving p = -1. Substituting p = -1, the limit as x → 0 is -5, and for 0 < x < 10^{-100}, the expression is extremely close to -5, within 0.1. Thus c = -5, an integer ≠ 0. The ordered pair is (p, c) = (-1, -5).",
